The success of the first season of “The Falcon and the Winter Soldier" — the finale premiered today — "can be seen as part of a wave of Black superheroes that have conquered our screens and comic book pages in recent years," writes 
@vvchambers
.  https://nyti.ms/32OJTfn

The murder conviction of a police officer is an exceedingly rare event. But Derek Chauvin’s conviction does not automatically signal a new era of police accountability, writes 
@DLeonhardt
. The George Floyd case was “the exception of all exceptions.” https://nyti.ms/3aw6Ubn

“My God, you are so lucky if you get to read these for the first time.” 
@taffyakner
 narrowed Philip Roth’s 31 books down into an essential reading list. https://nyti.ms/3gnttTf

“It had been over a year since I had been hit by the vibrations of a sizable contingent of musicians sitting in front of me,” our critic 
@zwoolfe
 writes of the New York Philharmonic’s first indoor live concert in 400 days, “and the sensation was sweet.”

. 
@Wirecutter
 taste tested the most popular ice cream sandwiches. A major classic didn't make the cut

"Is this year’s Olympic spirit one of resilience or of hubris? Is NBC covering — and participating in — a celebration or a catastrophe?" Our chief TV critic 
@poniewozik
 examines the #OpeningCeremony.

There’s no shortage of balms, candles, sprays, lotions, gadgets and gear designed to keep mosquitos away. 
@Wirecutter
 experts spent 55 hours trying to find the best solution.

White sharks are hunting along Cape Cod's beaches. What will it take to keep people safe? Read 
@cjchivers
’ cover story in 
@NYTMag
. 
https://nytimes.com/interactive/2021/10/20/magazine/sharks-cape-cod.html…

“I wish I lived in a world that considered disabled people from the very beginning of the design process and made products for us without charging a premium,” Claire Perlman writes for 
@wirecutter
.

The global supply chain crisis brought on by the pandemic may not be temporary.
@petersgoodman
, our global economics correspondent, went to one of the largest ports in the U.S. to see the havoc up close. Listen to today’s episode of The Daily.

Modern electronics can feel like they’re built for obsolescence. 
@wirecutter
’s audio and video experts offer tips on how to shop for headphones, speakers and TVs you won’t have to replace before you’re ready.

In today's NYT Parenting newsletter, 
@JessGrose
 asks: How do we know for sure that social media is worse for teen girls than traditional media was for previous generations?

A great air purifier can reduce allergens such as pollen and mold spores in your home, and can even remove wildfire smoke and virus particles from the air. After testing 47 different machines, here's what 
@wirecutter
 recommends.

Why is hunger increasing around the world? One reason is the rising cost of fertilizer. Many countries can't afford it, and the war in Ukraine is making things worse. Listen to the full conversation with 
@arappeport
, 
@Lattif
, 
@MujMash
 and @DavidMalpassWBG.

Newer investors have lost a lot of money in the crypto crash. And while those who bought Bitcoin years ago are still sitting on profits, says 
@eringriffith
, will they hold on? Listen to the full tech and crypto conversation with 
@sheeraf
 and 
@yaffebellany
. https://nyti.ms/3odG52e

Crypto has plunged as investors fled all risky assets, but it is also facing its own unique problems, says 
@yaffebellany
. Listen to the full conversation about crypto and the tech economy with 
@sheeraf
 and 
@eringriffith
. https://nyti.ms/3PnrH3n

From 
