@kateconger
 said. Listen to the whole conversation with 
@sheeraf
 and 
@LaurenSHirsch
. https://nyti.ms/3OHKwhB

When we skip a TV theme song, we are denying “the possibility of having this connection with a show that becomes bigger and more meaningful than the show itself,” 
@Wesley_Morris
 says on Still Processing. https://nyti.ms/3KaGiM7

Frederick Law Olmsted, the man behind many of the nation’s beloved public spaces, was born 200 years ago on April 26. His creations are more essential to modern life than ever. Times photographer 
@rfremson
 captured every season in spaces he designed. https://nyti.ms/3xW1x1w

On Still Processing, 
@Wesley_Morris
 talks to music critic Hanif Abdurraqib about TV theme songs – and the depth of connections and memories we're missing out on when we hit “skip intro.” Listen now. https://nyti.ms/3EDeaA9

